# Blue Oak Model Licence

Version 1.0.0

## Purpose

This licence gives everyone as much permission to work with this software as possible, while protecting contributors from liability.

## Acceptance

In order to receive this licence, you must agree to its rules. The rules of this licence are both obligations under that agreement and conditions to your licence. You must not do anything with this software that triggers a rule that you cannot or will not follow.

## Copyright

Each contributor licences you to do everything with this software that would otherwise infringe that contributor's copyright in it.

## Notices

You must ensure that everyone who gets a copy of any part of this software from you, with or without changes, also gets the text of this licence or a link to <https://blueoakcouncil.org/license/1.0.0>.

## Excuse

If anyone notifies you in writing that you have not complied with Notices, you can keep your licence by taking all practical steps to comply within 30 days after the notice. If you do not do so, your licence ends immediately.

## Patent

Each contributor licences you to do everything with this software that would otherwise infringe any patent claims they can licence or become able to licence.

## Reliability

No contributor can revoke this licence.

## No Liability

***As far as the law allows, this software comes as is, without any warranty or condition, and no contributor will be liable to anyone for any damages related to this software or this licence, under any kind of legal claim.***
